Passing by the proso- diacal objection, a graver difficulty has been found in the construction, “ Me in Apulian Vultur beyond the threshold of my nurse Apulia,'' The Apennine range, still called f“ Monte Vulture,'' was partly in Apulia, partly in Lucania. And Horace, Satire ii. 1, says it is doubtful whether he was a Lucanian or an Apulian, for the farmers of Venusia (his birthplace) ploughed the boundaries of both these provinces, Had he said “ Lucanian Vultur,’' “ beyond the threshold of Apulia,’' the passage, therefore, would have been clear 3 but “in Apulian Vultur, out of Apulia,'' is a puzzle for com- mentators.
